history.content: (Just a heads up: it's new and I think there are only 2-3 total students who have done it)

Hi! I'm an intended CogSci major trying to minor in CS, and since I took Math 55 before I decided to pursue the minor, I'm thinking of doing EECS 47F maybe next year to get the CS70 requirement done.

I saw already that to enroll I'd have to contact the CS70 staff of whichever semester I do it, but I just wanted to hear from any other students who may have already completed the course. There probably aren't too many people who have taken it since it's like a 'hidden' course sort of, but if there are any students who have taken it, I'd love to hear about your experience! Thanks :)
